pr_review_body:
@samuelcolvin, please beware that this PR introduces breaking changes

This was previously a valid usecase, but with these changes it will raise an error because second positional argument is now always passed to `getter_dict`:
```py
def test_custom_getter_dict():
    class TestCls:
        x = 1
        y = 2

    def custom_getter_dict(obj):
        assert isinstance(obj, TestCls)
        return {'x': 42, 'y': 24}

    class Model(BaseModel):
        x: int
        y: int
        class Config:
            orm_mode = True
            getter_dict = custom_getter_dict
    model = Model.from_orm(TestCls())
    assert model.dict() == {'x': 42, 'y': 24}
```

@fregataa 
There's a minor request about correcting type definition on the parameter.
Except that, It works fine.

> Do you know how this will impact cache keys with the argv no longer being deterministic? Iiuc, the local cache `CommandRunner` doesn't know about `bounded.rs` and simply sees the argv has changed.

@Eric-Arellano : The `bounded::CommandRunner` is always configured to be below all cache lookups. This is intended, because cache lookups should always be cheaper than actually running a process, and so aren't throttled/bounded.

It definitely is a fidgety though... the composition of `CommandRunner`s is powerful, but important to stack just-so.

The code looks good to me.  One potential concern is that if someone has `ray job submit` somewhere in a CI pipeline or something and it's acceptable for the Ray job to fail for whatever reason, then this PR would be a consequential breaking change.  

My gut says it's fine as long as we document it in the [CLI docs](https://docs.ray.io/en/latest/cluster/running-applications/job-submission/cli.html#ray-job-submit), would you mind adding it?

@akshay-anyscale @edoakes thoughts on the behavior change?

There was a bug in Android which also independently caused 'Not found' group members:
https://github.com/tinode/tindroid/commit/055f8b5db000d26fed1b4e55890f82a14b83f67e
Specifically changes like this fixed it:
```java
if (isP2PType()) {
    mTinode.updateUser(getName(), mDesc);
}
```
It probably exists in iOS too.

Looks good, some comments about the notebook:

- There are a few typos in the notebook and I suggest spellchecking it. The way I usually do it is a bit hacky but it works:

  * building documention pages
  * open html file into which notebook has been parsed
  * copy-paste its content to somewhere where Grammarly could review it.

- You can put `;` at the end of line `tiles_gdf.plot(ax=ax)`

- In the evalscript having 

  ```
  function evaluatePixel(samples) {
    for (let i = 0; i < samples.length; i++) {
      var sample = samples[i];
      return [f*sample.B08, f*sample.B04, f*sample.B03, sample.dataMask];
    }
  ```
  
  should be completely the same as 
  
  ```
  function evaluatePixel(sample) {
    return [f*sample.B08, f*sample.B04, f*sample.B03, sample.dataMask];
    }
  ```
  
  In both cases you return the first sample.

@frgfm Thanks for the feedback. You got a point that other model builders receive this as option but I'm not sure this was intentional or the side-effect of just grabbing `kwargs` and dumping them to the model class. 

My understanding is that the moment you start fiddling with this, you are advised to use the more powerful class API. This is why all the examples on our documentation that shows you how to overwrite the `AnchorGenerator` suggest that you should construct the model via the class API. Example:
https://github.com/pytorch/vision/blob/588e9b5ed7e2327f9bf5b2136b8c5fd0a85a62d8/torchvision/models/detection/faster_rcnn.py#L123-L141

Irrespective to the above, if we were to allow overwrites in this method, the patch needs to ported also on the prototype area:
https://github.com/pytorch/vision/blob/588e9b5ed7e2327f9bf5b2136b8c5fd0a85a62d8/torchvision/prototype/models/detection/faster_rcnn.py#L137-L146

@fmassa could you give your input on whether offering the ability to overwrite the `AnchorGenerator` from the model builder was intended when the method was introduced?
